            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-1a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] drought </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en">rain dew will not fall. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en">sun and moon will miss their (correct) time. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en">sprouts and grass will be abundant. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en">??? objects, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en">residing seclusion. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-2a.1" xml:lang="en">there will be drought and it will not rain, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en">yet the pool will not dry up. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en">one must cultivate oneself to the utmost, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en">waiting for the right time and then rise. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-3a.1" xml:lang="en">soft (delightful?) orchid! </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en">[...] shake and fall, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en">and still not losing its fragrance </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en">its fragrance will brim, its quiet will fills (the air?) (again) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-3a.5" xml:lang="en">and get to be heard about throughout the four quarters </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en">residing in secluded valley (?) </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-4a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] damage. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-4a.2" xml:lang="en">mole crickets, ants and poisonous snakes </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-4a.3" xml:lang="en">will approach the masses (?) and obtain their intent. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-4a.4" xml:lang="en">they will opppose and alienate the enactment of the Dao (?) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-4a.5" xml:lang="en">make damage without limits (?) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-4a.6" xml:lang="en">then the orchid (will again?) preside over virtue. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-4a.7" xml:lang="en">obtaining [...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-5a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] damage. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-5a.2" xml:lang="en">mole crickets, ants and poisonous snakes </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-5a.3" xml:lang="en">will approach the masses (?) and obtain their intent. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-5a.4" xml:lang="en">they will opppose and alienate the enactment of the Dao (?) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-5a.5" xml:lang="en">make damage without limits (?) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-5a.6" xml:lang="en">then the orchid (will again?) preside over virtue. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-5a.7" xml:lang="en">obtaining [...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-6a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] years before (?) its frugality (?) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-6a.2" xml:lang="en">beauty afterwards (??) its impermanence (?) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-6a.3" xml:lang="en">as an orchid without fragrance </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-6a.4" xml:lang="en">one trusts the foaminess (?) of the orchid (??) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-6a.5" xml:lang="en">when winds and drought not bringning damage, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-6a.6" xml:lang="en">the celestial way has surpassed it (??) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-6a.7" xml:lang="en">sprouts and grass are about to rise, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0079_tls_001-6a.8" xml:lang="en">and so they will meet their time (?). </seg>
                </p>

